The paper deals with predicting movement of objects in a dynamic environment, which is a key challenge in robotics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper proposes a multi-layer LSTM autoencoder network that predicts future frames for a robot navigating in a dynamic environment with moving obstacles. This involves processing image frames, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves training a neural network, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper proposes using the predicted frames in a reinforcement learning framework, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with a dynamic environment, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
